@baracuda40 you are correct wind turbines can go on a roof however, I'm looking at it from a home enthusiasts point of view. If you want decent output from a roof turbine you have to spend serious money which for most home makers is out of their limit. 
£ for £ in the uk urban environment I would still say solar (until Rob makes an awesome 3d printed system 😊) Provides better £/w value.

Just as an additional note, I did have a turbine mounted to my house as that's how my turbine project started as I was inspired by one of robs videos 😁 the small vibrations from a turbine have a detrimental structural impact which unless you've been there and done that... you wouldn't know the impact of hence why the turbine got moved to an 11m mount with stays.
